title: Force Lunch Data Update
name: Force_Lunch_Data_Update
description: Although downloading the lunch data happens automagically everyday at 6:00 AM server time, this endpoint will force the download of the data.

title: Get Lunch Menu
name: Get_Lunch_Menu
description: This endpoint returns the lunch menu for a given day (only works up to the end of the current week). It defaults to the current day.

title: Get Lunch Menu
name: Get_Lunch_Menu
description: This endpoint, when loaded in a web browser, will return the image of the lunch menu of the date specified, or today if none is specified. If it is a weekend, it defaults to monday.

examples.title: Success-Response:
examples.content: "There is no example. It returns the lunch menu."

Success 200.description: The Lunch API is in BETA. The functionality and structure of endpoints and routes WILL change.

title: All Periods
name: _All_Periods_
description: This endpoint returns an array of all of the periods in a date, or today if none is specified.

Success 200.description: Start time of period in UTC timezone
End time of period in UTC timezone

Error 4xx.description: The date query was formatted incorrectly or is an invalid range.

title: Day Type (Letterday)
name: _DayType_
description: This endpoint returns the letter day of a given date, or now if none specified.

Error 4xx.description: The date query was formatted incorrectly or is an invalid range.

title: GetToken
name: _Get_Token_
description: This endpoint returns a user's token after authentication.

Error 4xx.description: The user with the given username/password does not exist.

title: Next Occurance
name: _Next_Occurrence_
description: This endpoint returns the next occurrence(s) of a specified day type or period (not including the current occurrence, if applicable).

Required.description: A string specifying the type of requested resource
A string specifying the type of requested resource e.g "A", "Period 1", "Advisory Office Hours"

Parameter.description: the maximum number of future occurrences to be returned
an ISO 8061 date string to search forward from

Success 200.description: Start time of period in UTC timezone
End time of period in UTC timezone

Error 4xx.description: A type or identifier is missing or invalid

title: Period
name: _Period_
description: This endpoint returns the current period if no date is specified, or the period at the specified date and time. If no period exists, an empty object will be returned.

Success 200.description: Start time of period in UTC timezone
End time of period in UTC timezone

Error 4xx.description: The date query was formatted incorrectly or is an invalid range.

title: Register Account
name: _Register_Account_
description: This endpoint creates a user account in the database and returns a token.
